Structural and Dybamical Divergence Analysis - Comparisons

Introduction

We study the evolutionary divergence of proteins using the mutational model LF-ENM and the selection model Stress Model. We compare simulated mutants with experimental data. In this report we compare the results obtained for diferrent families, using different R0s, and considering two different enm: CA (one node per site enm model: CA) and CM (two nodes per site enm model: CA and CM of side chains). R0 used were 7.5, 10 and 12.5 for CA and 5, 7.5 and 10 for CM.

We analyzed the following families:

## [5] "phoslip"        "fabp"           "rrm"            "serinProteases"
